setup mit CENTOS07


1. yum install -y gcc-c++ make
2. curl -sL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_6.x | sudo -E bash -
3. yum install nodejs
4. node -v 
5. npm -v

6. create a new file called test.js
fixture `My first fixture`
    .page `https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example`;

test('My first test', async t => {
    await t
        .typeText('#developer-name', 'Peter Parker')
        .click('#submit-button');
});

7. If you are running on a min vm, you will need to add a browser, if you have a dvd or full install you will have firefox, so the command
needed to get it up and running is 
testcafe firefox test.js
